Police &ldquo;A&rdquo; defended the Lakeside Hockey Tournament title after a hard fought 2-1 post match penalty flicks win over Police &ldquo;B&rdquo; at Jomo Kenyatta Sports Ground in Kisumu over the weekend.The win was not a walk in the park for the champions after the teams drew 3-3 at regulation time.Kelvin Oriema gave Police &ldquo;B&rdquo; the lead in the ninth minute but it was shortlived as Brian Saina equalised a minute later.Robert Masibo added the second for Police &ldquo;A&rdquo; in the 14th minute.In the second half, Moses Cheptailen equalised in the 20th minute. Kelvin Kanu made it 3-2 a minute later before Titus Kimutai pushed the match into overdrive at the stroke of full time.In the penalty flicks, Willis Okeyo and Calvince Kanu converted for Police &ldquo;A&rdquo; while Olira Echenje scored the only penalty for Police &ldquo;B&rdquo;.&ldquo;The match was tough, credit to our opponents but I am very happy we have defended our title. We are going back to training ahead of the club championship in January,&rdquo; said Police &ldquo;A&rdquo; captain Kennedy Sibweche.&ldquo;Kisumu has been a breeding ground for excellent hockey players for years but that has been deteriorating recently. We need to have this kind of tournament regularly as opposed to December to enable organisers tap and nurture talent,&rdquo; said Kenneth Kaunda who coaches Police &ldquo;B&rdquo;.He said the tournament is a major boost to their preparations for the club championship that will kick off on January 7, 2016.&ldquo;We have only two weeks to prepare for the tournament.We are going back to training before breaking camp for the Christmas holidays. We will then embark for final touches later on.&rdquo;Police &ldquo;A&rdquo; beat Arizona 2-0 in the first semi-final while Police &ldquo;B&rdquo; beat Western Jaguars 2-1.